arts.ttl: Exeter City 1 Cambridge United 0 - Grecians win again and rise up the table - Devon Live
arts.sum: Exeter City: (3-4-3) Joe Whitworth, Pierce Sweeney, Jack Fitzwater, Johnly Yfeko, Jack McMillan, Ryan Woodsm Ed Francis (Mustapha Carayol, 83),, Ilmari Niskanen, Jack Aitchison (Kamari Doyle, 72), Millenic Alli, Josh Magennis (Amani Richards, 36, Sonny Cox, 72) Exeter were on top but couldn’t grab a second before the break, with Richards and McMillan getting in each other’s way after Pierce Sweeney slid a ball through, while Johnly Yfeko headed straight into Reyes’ arms.

arts.ttl: Ryan Woods scores first goal in seven years to earn victory for Exeter
Exeter City Women want to return to winning ways
arts.sum: Valentine Pursey made an impressive impact at Hashtag United last season and has begun this season in goalscoring form, Bonnie Horwood adds experience to a young squad after her summer signing from Ipswich Town. Exeter City Women will be looking to return to winning ways as Billericay Town are the visitors to St James Park on Sunday afternoon, 2pm.

arts.ttl: Exeter City have to keep good run going against bottom side Cambridge United
arts.sum: The U’s arrive in Devon bottom of League One with just one point from their first eight league games, while they were just seconds away from a second point of the season in midweek before former Grecians striker Sam Nombe struck in injury time to earn Rotherham United a 1-0 win at the Abbey Stadium. In fact, it was this time last year that, after such an excellent start, City went on a 14-match sequence in League One in which they failed to win a single game.

arts.ttl: Exeter City already want to make Johnly Yfeko's loan permanent
arts.sum: EXETER City manager Gary Caldwell says that things are in place to turn Johnly Yfeko’s loan deal into something permanent with the young Rangers defender catching the eye in League One this season. “Johnly is a young player with a huge future and if we could tie him down to be a permanent player at this club, then I think it would be a brilliant thing to do,” he said.
